###SECTION:budget_rationale
The ${{ "{:,.0f}".format(monthly_budget_min) }}–${{ "{:,.0f}".format(monthly_budget_max) }} monthly budget is allocated with a primary-channel bias toward the highest-intent formats: {{ primary_channels[0] | replace("_", " ") | title }} and {{ primary_channels[1] | replace("_", " ") | title }} together account for approximately 60% of spend. This reflects the principle that bottom and mid-funnel channels should be fully funded before allocating to awareness and upper-funnel placements.

The remaining 40% is distributed across {{ primary_channels[2:] | join(", ") | replace("_", " ") }} for prospecting, retargeting, and retention. Budget will be reviewed at 30-day intervals; channels consistently underperforming against ROAS and CPA targets will have budget reallocated to outperforming placements within the same review cycle.

###LIST:risk_mitigations
- Platform policy changes (especially Meta and Google): Mitigation — diversified channel mix ensures no single platform accounts for more than 40% of spend. Creative library maintained to enable rapid response to policy-driven disapprovals.
- Attribution degradation (iOS privacy, cookie deprecation): Mitigation — server-side event tracking and GA4 data-driven attribution implemented from campaign launch. First-party data collection prioritised via email capture and CRM integration.
- Creative fatigue: Mitigation — structured A/B testing with mandatory 4-week creative rotation. Performance creative playbook developed from winning ad formats to accelerate future production cycles.

###SECTION:success_timeline
At 30 days, the focus is on data collection and baseline establishment — campaigns will be in learning phase, and performance metrics should not yet be evaluated against final KPI targets. At 60 days, the portfolio will have exited platform learning phases and optimisation decisions can be made with statistical confidence. Initial ROAS targets should be achievable for the bottom-funnel channels by this point. At 90 days, the full funnel — from awareness through conversion — will be operational and optimised. Blended ROAS targets, CPA goals, and monthly conversion volume targets should all be met or exceeded by the end of the 90-day ramp period, assuming budget continuity and timely creative delivery.
